Name: Statue of Gemeh-su as a Falcon
Description: This is one of 28 gilded wooden statuettes of deities wrapped in shrouds to look like mummies. They were kept in shrines placed in the tomb to protect King Tutankhamun during his journey in the underworld. This statuette represents Gemeh-su as a falcon sitting on an insignia, or symbol of rank. His back is adorned with the flail and the Neheh sign
